RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s King Salman received a written message from Kuwaiti Crown Prince Sheikh Meshal Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber Al-Sabah on Sunday. The message, concerning strong bilateral relations and ways to support and enhance them in various fields, was received by the Kingdom’s Deputy Foreign Minister Waleed bin Abdulkarim Al-Khuraiji in Riyadh during a meeting with the Kuwaiti ambassador to Saudi Arabia. During the meeting, Al-Khuraiji and Sheikh Ali Al-Khaled Al-Jaber Al-Sabah discussed bilateral relations and ways to enhance them in various fields, and exchanged views on issues of common concern.